				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Damage is capped by levels anyway which tends to make the recommended levels for damage on weapons somewhat superfluous. The fact is, even at a full 11 dmg, a level 20 isn't going to do significantly more damage than if the weapon damage was 4 or 5</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Actually, I beg to differ <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Even at level 1 an 11 damage weapon will kick the crap out of a 4 or 5 damage weapon.
<br />

<br />
The max hit at 1 is 20 from the cap,
<br />
11x2=22 max hit capped at 20
<br />
5x2 = 10 max hit
<br />

<br />
So at level 1 youll be able to hit for 20 with an 11 whereas a 5 will only hit for 10 max.
<br />

<br />
This is assuming unbuffed or not severely buffed and average stats.
<br />

<br />
At 10 the 20 damage cap is lifted to 30, so the 11 damage will begin to hit for 22 max and the 5 will still be stuck at 10 damage.
<br />

<br />
It just goes up from there.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
